analysis: The documents primarily concern the transfer, restoration, or reservation of land, often involving military reservations, lighthouse reservations, or other government-controlled areas. Many documents involve the Territory of Hawaii and Alaska, with specific geographic coordinates and detailed descriptions of the land parcels. The purpose of these actions is often to either return land to the Territory/State for public use (e.g., roads, parks) or to adjust boundaries and control for military or other federal purposes. There's a recurring theme of adapting land use to changing needs, whether it's restoring land no longer needed for military purposes or reserving land for new federal projects.
title: Land Management and Boundary Adjustments in Hawaii and Alaska
